						<div class="postbody">I only see this effect here when I considerably turn down brightness.<br /><br />I would say it varies from TV to TV. Only other TV I have here is an LG 100Hz wonder that deinterlaces any input... digitally... with rather blurry result and input lag, making games hard to play.<br />EDIT: I tried it in 50Hz, and I see the effect at near normal brightness too. I still had to lower it a bit. It is said the TVs in EU have longer glow on the phosphors, and it is probably what is happening over here, that diminishes the effect (and which is why I said that it should not really make the image brighter...).</div>

					
